                     <p>Italian notation on 3 or 4 lines; 2 or 3 dry point, one red (F) and sometimes one yellow (C); up to fol.47<hi rend="superscript">v</hi> the notation resembles the North Italian system, from fol.60 onwards the Beneventan.</p>
